poor thing,” she purred. “I’m so sorry for you, for your brother.… Heavens, what unhappy people there are in the world! He mustn’t die, it is never impossible to save a person.”

“He can’t be saved,” said I, with what is called, I believe, a bitter smile. “He is determined to die on his birthday; the ninth of March—that is to say, the day after tomorrow; and the President of the State could not prevent it. Suicide is the worst form of self-indulgence. All one can do is to c